**Dimension:** Performance & Complexity
**Lint:** clippy::useless_vec

## Violation
A `vec![a, b, c]` used only by-reference (e.g. `.iter()` / `.contains()` / slice coercion) heap-allocates pointlessly. A stack array `[a, b, c]` provides the same slice API with zero allocation.

## Locations
- src/compaction.rs: 777, 1051

## Mandated Refactor
```rust
// Before
for x in vec![1, 2, 3] { ... }
// After
for x in [1, 2, 3] { ... }
// Or if a slice is needed:
let slice: &[T] = &[a, b, c];
```
